timeline.bodyText:
If I'm not mistaken the propose of the expression Stream.of(lt,gt,nullFilter).filter(Objects::nonNull).collect(Collectors.toList())  is to get rid of nullFilter if it's NULL, I think it would be more efficient and (arguably) clear to do something like this instead:
if (isNillable(pName)) {
    // the property may have a NULL value, we need to vouch for it
    nullFilter = ff.isNull(pb.getExpression());
    return ff.or(lt, gt, nullFilter);
}
// the property value cannot be null
return ff.or(lt, gt);

